<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9445] Admin requests are retried by CloudSolrClient and LBHttpSolrClient on failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9445</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Another bug found during &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9438&quot; title=&quot;Shard split can lose data&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-9438&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-9438&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I saw that shard split requests were being retried more times than the attempts made by the test. I traced it to LBHttpSolrClient which retries automatically on 404 or 403 or 503 or 500 errors except when the request is an update.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Each admin request is retried on failure as many times as the number of live nodes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
